originalText.text:
I found a new obsession in Moynihan Hall this week, thanks to my friend Darren who hooks me up with THE BEST ICE CREAM at Jacob's Pickles (Pickle & Popcorn, y'all... you just must)! So much good food there!

Moynihan Food Hall can get packed and finding a seat for just my own little self was a challenge, but to be fair it was about rush hour!

My buddy Darren pointed out some delicious options for me at The Irish Exit! I tried the Devils on Horseback. I hope I'm remembering the name right because TBH I lovingly renamed them "Devil Doobies" when I described them to my hubby! I'll say there are nuts, dates, goat cheese, AND BACON involved in this surprising treat! I know, I know... Devil Doobies and pickles and popcorn ice cream.... We don't need to talk about what a strange combination this is, ok. It's more than fine. It's perfection. I went home happy from Moynihan and that's what counts!
